de.dhbwka.swe.utils.util

Interface IPropertyManagerOLD


  • public interface IPropertyManagerOLD
    The Interface IPropertyManager declares the methods to access a basic property manager that provides the application with configuration values that can be stored.

    • Method Detail

      • getProperties

        String[] getProperties(String propertyName,
                       int min,
                       int max)
        Get properties of the properties file identified by a common property name and a consecutive number and limited to a given value range
        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property contained in the properties file in the form:
        propertyNameX + "=" + propertyValue (where X is a number starting with 1...) (example: ExampleProperty1="something", where the property name is "ExampleProperty").
        min - the minimal value that should be taken into account.
        max - the maximal value that should be taken into account.
        Returns:
        all values of the properties that start with the name given by propertyName and are within the given range.

      • getProperties

        String[] getProperties(String propertyName,
                       String[] defaultValues,
                       int min,
                       int max)
        Get properties of the properties file identified by a common property name and a consecutive number and limited to a given value range
        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property contained in the properties file in the form:
        propertyNameX + "=" + propertyValue (where X is a number starting with 1...) (example: ExampleProperty1="something", where the property name is "ExampleProperty").
        defaultValues - default values that will be returned, if no Property with the given name exists.
        min - the minimal value that should be taken into account.
        max - the maximal value that should be taken into account.
        Returns:
        all values of the properties that start with the name given by propertyName and are within the given range.

      • getIntegerProperty

        int getIntegerProperty(String propertyName)
        Get an Integer (int) property of the properties file
        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property contained in the properties file in the form:
        propertyName + "=" + propertyValue (example: ExampleProperty=123, here the property name is "ExampleProperty").
        Returns:
        the value of the property with the name propertyName. Looking at the example above, the value returned is 123. If no property was found, the default value returned is 0.

      • getIntegerProperty

        int getIntegerProperty(String propertyName,
                       int defaultValue,
                       boolean getBiggerValue)
        Get an Integer (int) property of the properties file
        Parameters:
        propertyName - the name of the property contained in the properties file in the form:
        propertyName + "=" + propertyValue (example: ExampleProperty="123", here the property name is "ExampleProperty").
        defaultValue - a default value that will be returned, if no Property with the given name exists.
        getBiggerValue - get the bigger (true) or the smaller (false) value of both (stored or default value)
        Returns:
        the value of the property with the name propertyName. If no Property is given, 0 is returned and a warning will be printed
